<BLOCK1><TI>CLAIM</TI>
<P>1. The Plaintiff, Vivian Bercovici (&ldquo;the Plaintiff&rdquo;), claims against the Attorney General of Canada (the &ldquo;Attorney General&rdquo;):
<P1>a) A declaration that the Attorney General breached its fiduciary duties to the Plaintiff;</P1>
<P1>b) Damages for breach of fiduciary duty in the amount of $1,000,000;</P1>
<P1>c) A declaration that the Attorney General breached its contractual duty of good faith and honesty in contractual performance to the Plaintiff;</P1>
<P1>d) Damages for the breach of contractual duty of good faith and honesty and contractual performance in the amount of $1,000,000;</P1>
<P1>e) Judgment in the amount of $31,974.32 for the Plaintiff's pension monies and interest still being withheld by the Attorney General;</P1>
<P1>f) In the alternative to (d), moral damages for the bad faith manner of termination of the Plaintiff's Appointment in the amount of $1,000,000.00;</P1>
<P1>g) Punitive damages in the amount of $5,000,000;</P1>
<P1>h) Pre-judgment and post-judgment interest in accordance with the provisions of the <EM>Courts of Justice Act</EM>, R.S.O. 1990, c. C. 43, as amended;</P1>
<P1>i) Her costs of this action on a substantial indemnity basis, plus HST; and</P1>
<P1>j) Such further and other relief as this Honourable Court may deem just.</P1></P>
<P>2. The Plaintiff claims against the individual Defendant, Mark Gwozdecky (&ldquo;Mr. Gwozdecky&rdquo;):
<P1>a) Damages for the tort of intentional infliction of mental suffering in the amount of $500,000;</P1>
<P1>b) Her costs of this action on a substantial indemnity basis, plus HST; and</P1>
<P1>c) Such further and other relief as this Honourable Court may deem just.</P1></P>
<P>3. The Plaintiff claims against the individual Defendant, Daniel Jean (&ldquo;Mr. Jean&rdquo;):
<P1>a) Damages for the tort of intentional infliction of mental suffering in the amount of $500,000;</P1>
<P1>b) Her costs of this action on a substantial indemnity basis, plus HST; and</P1>
<P1>c) Such further and other relief as this Honourable Court may deem just.</P1></P>
<P>4. The Plaintiff claims against the individual Defendant, Alexandra Bugailiskis (&ldquo;Ms. Bugailiskis&rdquo;):
<P1>a) Damages for the tort of intentional infliction of mental suffering in the amount of $500,000;</P1>
<P1>b) Her costs of this action on a substantial indemnity basis, plus HST; and</P1>
