<BLOCK1><TI>ORDER</TI>
<P><BOLD>THIS MOTION</BOLD>, made by the Plaintiff, to amend the title of proceeding to add Katie Telford, Mark Gwozdecky, Daniel Jean, Barbara Richardson and Alexandra Bugailiskis as defendants to this action <EM>nunc pro tunc</EM>, was heard February 25, 2019, at 393 University Avenue, Toronto.</P>
<P><BOLD>UPON READING</BOLD> the motion records of the Plaintiff and of the Defendant filed on the motion and on hearing the submissions of counsel for the Plaintiff and counsel for Katie Telford, Mark Gwozdecky, Daniel Jean, Barbara Richardson, Alex Bugailiskis and the Defendant, the Attorney General of Canada, and the Court having been advised that counsel have agreed on the disposition of costs of the motion:</P>
<P>1. <BOLD>THIS COURT ORDERS</BOLD> that the motion to add Mark Gwozdecky, Daniel Jean, Alex Bugailiskis, and Barbara Richardson as defendants to this action is hereby dismissed.</P>
<P>2. <BOLD>THIS COURT ORDERS</BOLD> that the plaintiff is granted leave to add Katie Telford as a defendant to this action based upon allegations of bad faith conduct only.</P>
<P>3. <BOLD>THIS COURT ORDERS</BOLD> that the plaintiff pay costs of this motion fixed in the amount of $3,000.00 to the Defendant, the Attorney General of Canada in any event of the cause.</P>
<P><UNDER>MASTER ANDREW T. GRAHAM</UNDER></P>
